🚢 Titanic Dataset Analysis using Power BI

This project focuses on analyzing the famous Titanic dataset using Power BI to uncover meaningful insights about passenger survival patterns and the factors that influenced the tragedy of 1912.

The dataset includes information about passengers such as age, gender, ticket class, fare, family size, and survival status, making it ideal for data exploration, visualization, and storytelling.

📊 Project Overview

Using Power BI, the raw Titanic dataset was transformed into an interactive dashboard to perform exploratory data analysis (EDA) and identify hidden patterns in the data.

The analysis primarily investigates how different factors such as social class, gender, and age impacted survival rates during the disaster.

🧹 Data Preparation

Before visualization, the dataset was cleaned and transformed using Power Query, including:

Handling missing values (especially in Age and Cabin fields)
Removing or correcting inconsistent data
Creating new calculated columns (e.g., Age Groups, Family Size)
Formatting categorical variables for better analysis
📈 Key Visualizations in Power BI

The dashboard includes several interactive visuals such as:

Survival rate by gender
Survival rate by passenger class (1st, 2nd, 3rd)
Age distribution of survivors and non-survivors
Fare distribution analysis
Family size impact on survival
Interactive filters and slicers for deeper exploration
🔍 Key Insights

From the analysis, several important patterns were discovered:

Women and children had a significantly higher survival rate
Passengers in 1st class had better chances of survival compared to 3rd class
Higher fare payment was generally associated with higher survival probability
Survival chances were influenced by social and economic status
📌 Tools & Technologies
Power BI Desktop
Power Query (Data Cleaning & Transformation)
DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)
Kaggle Titanic Dataset
🎯 Conclusion

This project demonstrates how Power BI can transform historical raw data into interactive and meaningful insights. It highlights the importance of data visualization in understanding patterns, making decisions, and telling data-driven stories.
